FBIS4-10518 "drlat072_a_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Robaina Meets Argentina's Menem, Senators Robaina Meets Argentina's Menem, Senators FL1404000494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 13 Apr 94 FL1404000494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] A note from PRENSA LATINA says that Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina today received, in Buenos Aires, the Illustrious Visitor decoration which was granted to him by the deliberative council of the Argentine capital. The ceremony took place during a 48-hour visit by Robaina to Argentina during which he also met with the provisional president of the Senate, Eduardo Menem. It has been reported that legislators from all the political parties represented in the Senate participated in this meeting, which has been described as friendly. Upon welcoming Roberto Robaina, Eduardo Menem ratified a resolution approved by the Senate last year in which the Senate came out in favor of a cessation of the U.S. blockade of Cuba.
